  "AI content payment is not merely a copyright or transaction-efficiency problem; it is a question of political-economic legitimacy. As AI valuations reach hundreds of billions, society asks why the gains from public web content and human knowledge accrue to a few firms. The paper proposes a six-layer tiered data market — from free public content through scarce verified datasets to public benefit-sharing — and defines the AI network democratic economy: rights, pricing, participation, auditability, and returns, each democratized through machine-readable protocols like AICR/AICL.": "Malipo ya maudhui kwa AI si tatizo la hakimiliki au ufanisi wa miamala pekee; ni suala la uhalali wa kiuchumi-kisiasa. Thamani za AI zinapofikia mamia ya mabilioni, jamii inauliza kwa nini faida zitokanazo na maudhui ya mtandao wa umma na maarifa ya binadamu zinaishia kwa makampuni machache. Waraka huu unapendekeza soko la data lenye ngazi sita — kuanzia maudhui huria ya umma hadi seti za data adimu zilizothibitishwa hadi ugawanaji wa manufaa ya umma — na kufafanua uchumi wa mtandao wa AI wa kidemokrasia: haki, upangaji bei, ushiriki, uwezekano wa kukaguliwa, na marejesho, kila kimoja kikiwa cha kidemokrasia kupitia itifaki zinazosomeka na mashine kama AICR/AICL.",
